    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-05-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-05-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="543"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. F. W. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord
                        Lyons</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-05-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 30, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt
                    of your note of the 28th instant, in which, with reference to the case of Mr.
                    John Hardcastle, inquiry is made whether the report is true that that
                    unfortunate man has met with his death in the Carroll prison; and if so, what
                    were the circumstances that led to so deplorable a result.</p>
                <p>In reply, I have the honor to inform you that no time has been lost in
                    communicating a copy of your note to Major L. C. Turner, judge advocate, with a
                    view to an investigation of the matter and a report of the result of that
                    investigation.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with high consideration, your lordship’s obedient
                    servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F. W. SEWARD, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
